"The vote will take place before the end of February 2013," informed Nacher.
Controversial EU regulations include, for example, the requirement to add bio-components to fuels, which has adverse environmental consequences, or the ban on the use of reliable mercury thermometers, solely because they contain a relatively small amount of a hazardous substance, or the hen cage size directive, which has led to higher egg prices.
Criticism has also been expressed in the past about the de facto prohibition of the use of the term "butter to spread" or the withdrawal of the sale of conventional bulbs.
Quality bananas must be 14 centimetres tall.
