The European Commission defended itself by arguing that it was merely harmonising non-homogeneous national standards that complicated trade.
The standards for fruit and vegetables have been relaxed despite opposition from some States, claiming that the existing directives result in a waste of food.
The first prize may be awarded in this investigation to last year's EU regulation that must include on inflatable balloons a warning that children under 8 years of age must not inflate without adult supervision.
The EU referred to an American survey that found balloons among toys to be the leading cause of child deaths from suffocation.
