I'm in the small town of Fagernes, about three hours from Oslo.
It snows, the landscape is spectacular - and this odor, omnipresent, permeates the air.
The rakfisk consists of trout sprinkled with salt and fermented in water for a duration - depending on the smell you want it to exhale - that can go up to a year.
When darkness settles down and it's cold, Norwegians gather en masse to attend a festival that takes place here in Fagernes, dedicated to this incredible culinary specialty.
